Postoperative management in healthcare is essential for the successful recovery of patients after surgery. The postoperative management market is segmented into postoperative pain management, wound care management, and medication management. Postoperative pain management involves interventions such as medications and physical therapy to provide pain relief to patients. Wound care management focuses on preventing infections and promoting proper healing of surgical wounds. Medication management includes administering prescribed medications and monitoring for potential drug interactions to ensure optimal recovery.

